        "synopsis": {
            "value": "Seok Ji-Won (Ju Ji-Hoon) and Yoon Ji-Won (Jung Yu-Mi) were born on the same day and in the same town. They also share the same given name of Ji-Won, but their families have been enemies for generations. They studied at the same schools, but, they were rivals and growled whenever they made eye contact.\n\nDuring Seok Ji-Won’s student days, he was a cheerful person and good with education and sports. Due to his family's situation, he left his hometown with his family. Now, Seok Ji-Won is an adult and works as senior managing director at Seokban Construction. He returns to his hometown as the chairman of Dokmok High School, which he and Yoon Ji-Won attended. There, he reunites with Yoon Ji-Won, who works as a PE teacher. During her student days, she was called \"Mad Dog,\" because she couldn't tolerate injustice or bad practices. She had to confront these situations and try to correct them. As she experienced more difficulties while becoming an adult, her \"Mad Dog\" tendencies have gone into hibernation. After reuniting with Seok Ji-Won, the old Yoon Ji-Won begins to emerge again.",
            "source": "asianwiki",
            "source_link": "https://asianwiki.com/Love_Your_Enemy"
        },
